00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:56,724
A week after that, Gina was back in school,
studying harder than before...

258
00:17:57,532 --> 00:18:01,366
...coming home every night,
trying to take care of me and Ritchie.

259
00:18:02,812 --> 00:18:04,404
She's still doing it.

260
00:18:04,732 --> 00:18:06,324
I apologize.

261
00:18:10,012 --> 00:18:13,004
But as you may have guessed...

262
00:18:13,812 --> 00:18:15,370
...l am crazy about my Gina.

263
00:18:15,452 --> 00:18:17,568
My God, I am so thrilled...

264
00:18:17,772 --> 00:18:21,447
...she met someone who knows
exactly how she deserves to be treated.

265
00:18:21,732 --> 00:18:22,642
Right.

266
00:18:22,732 --> 00:18:24,324
Like a fucking princess.

267
00:18:25,812 --> 00:18:30,124
Mr. Vitale, I think I should really tell you
about what happened tonight.

268
00:18:32,892 --> 00:18:36,089
I got a confession to make.
I already know.

269
00:18:36,652 --> 00:18:39,120
-You do?
-Well, her doorman called me.

270
00:18:40,652 --> 00:18:45,168
When he called with the good news,
I knew this Michael, he's a gentleman.

271
00:18:45,372 --> 00:18:47,840
He's coming to ask for my daughter's hand.

272
00:18:49,932 --> 00:18:51,160
Go ahead.

273
00:18:58,252 --> 00:18:59,446
May l...

274
00:19:00,252 --> 00:19:03,483
...please have your daughter's hand
in marriage...

275
00:19:04,572 --> 00:19:05,846
...Mr. Vitale?

276
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,046
Frank?

277
00:19:12,372 --> 00:19:13,361
Dad.

278
00:19:13,732 --> 00:19:14,721
Yes.

279
00:19:15,812 --> 00:19:17,211
What a kid.

280
00:19:33,292 --> 00:19:35,123
I'm sleeping, Daddy.

281
00:19:38,012 --> 00:19:39,001
It's me.

282
00:19:47,252 --> 00:19:48,890
I love you so much.

283
00:19:49,572 --> 00:19:51,164
Well, I love you.

284
00:19:51,452 --> 00:19:53,522
Then why did you have to do this?

285
00:19:54,732 --> 00:19:57,166
Everything was perfect.
Why did you have to ruin it?

286
00:19:57,452 --> 00:19:59,124
I didn't mean to.

287
00:19:59,932 --> 00:20:01,160
I just thought--

288
00:20:01,252 --> 00:20:03,482
I know! And I do!

289
00:20:03,892 --> 00:20:06,167
I do so much!

290
00:20:06,812 --> 00:20:08,131
Well, that's great.

291
00:20:08,212 --> 00:20:10,362
That's fantastic.

292
00:20:10,572 --> 00:20:12,608
But I can't! l....

293
00:20:13,372 --> 00:20:14,487
I just can't!

294
00:20:14,572 --> 00:20:16,290
Gina, I'm not following.

295
00:20:18,652 --> 00:20:21,803
-What's happening?
-I can't talk about this in the house.

296
00:20:23,132 --> 00:20:24,804
So where are we going?

297
00:20:25,412 --> 00:20:26,208
Out.

298
00:20:27,252 --> 00:20:29,402
Right. Nowhere too dressy, I hope.

299
00:20:40,732 --> 00:20:43,292
I can't marry you, because of my father.

300
00:20:44,532 --> 00:20:45,681
Your father?

301
00:20:48,612 --> 00:20:50,330
I just met your father.

302
00:20:51,012 --> 00:20:52,240
I loved him.

303
00:20:53,212 --> 00:20:57,046
Well, I needed this address,
so I went to The The Trattoria.

304
00:20:57,252 --> 00:20:59,129
I met some of your relations.

305
00:21:00,852 --> 00:21:02,331
Keep walking.

306
00:21:04,052 --> 00:21:07,283
So who'd you meet? Nice Uncle Vito?

307
00:21:07,772 --> 00:21:10,809
Full name: Vito Graziosi.
That ring any bells?

308
00:21:11,452 --> 00:21:12,726
Was it boxing?

309
00:21:12,932 --> 00:21:17,050
Vito "The Butcher" Graziosi.
He's the head of the Graziosi crime family.

310
00:21:17,252 --> 00:21:18,685
Did you meet Johnny?

311
00:21:18,772 --> 00:21:22,924
Johnny Graziosi just finished eight years
in Sing Sing for loansharking.

312
00:21:23,132 --> 00:21:24,201
Vinnie?

313
00:21:24,532 --> 00:21:28,241
Vinnie "The Shrimp" D'Agostino!
Twenty years for double murder!

314
00:21:28,732 --> 00:21:30,290
Do you get the picture?

315
00:21:30,372 --> 00:21:32,567
I don't understand. Are you saying...

316
00:21:32,652 --> 00:21:35,246
...your dad's some kind of Mob caterer?

317
00:21:36,492 --> 00:21:40,087
My father was in prison
till I was eight, Michael.

318
00:21:40,812 --> 00:21:42,530
He's one of them.

319
00:21:49,532 --> 00:21:50,521
Wow.

320
00:21:52,892 --> 00:21:54,803
Just keep walking.

321
00:21:57,332 --> 00:22:01,245
I should've told you months ago
or just walked away.

322
00:22:01,612 --> 00:22:04,922
Normally I would have,
but I couldn't because I was so happy.

323
00:22:05,132 --> 00:22:07,202
Listen. I don't want to marry your father.

324
00:22:07,292 --> 00:22:11,285
But you will, Michael, whether you like it
or not. Him and his friends.

325
00:22:11,492 --> 00:22:13,562
I can't let that happen, because I love you.

326
00:22:13,652 --> 00:22:16,291
Everything they touch ends up spoiled
and corrupted.

327
00:22:16,372 --> 00:22:21,082
Wait a minute! This is ridiculous.
For a start, I might not be corruptible.

328
00:22:21,812 --> 00:22:24,610
It's a little favor,
a tiny lie and you're theirs.

329
00:22:25,292 --> 00:22:26,964
Believe me, I've seen it.

330
00:22:27,052 --> 00:22:29,043
No, I'm sorry.

331
00:22:29,532 --> 00:22:31,602
It's just over, Michael.

332
00:22:35,092 --> 00:22:36,366
Well, no.

333
00:22:37,852 --> 00:22:42,482
I've waited all my life to find someone
I love as much as I love you.

334
00:22:42,652 --> 00:22:47,282
And I'm just not gonna let this
or anyone come between us.

335
00:22:47,492 --> 00:22:51,371
Not Vito "The Butcher"
or Vinnie "The Baker"...

336
00:22:51,572 --> 00:22:55,531
...or anyone involved in any kind
of food preparation. End of story.

337
00:22:55,732 --> 00:22:57,529
But you don't know how clever they are.

338
00:22:57,612 --> 00:23:01,605
You do, presumably, and you can tell me.
We can do this together.

339
00:23:04,612 --> 00:23:06,125
Completely together?

340
00:23:06,332 --> 00:23:08,402
Completely. I swear.

341
00:23:09,772 --> 00:23:11,490
Now just give in.

342
00:23:12,452 --> 00:23:13,771
Marry me.

343
00:23:18,092 --> 00:23:19,002
Yes.

344
00:23:23,332 --> 00:23:25,846
Smile, you're engaged!

345
00:23:26,532 --> 00:23:29,808
Great. Now just Gina and Michael.
Over here, I think--

346
00:23:30,012 --> 00:23:32,162
Happy engagement, you guys!

347
00:23:32,972 --> 00:23:34,724
-How's this?
-Okay, say "cheese."

348
00:23:34,812 --> 00:23:35,688
Cheese!

349
00:23:35,772 --> 00:23:38,161
You're right, he really does talk funny.

350
00:23:38,252 --> 00:23:40,720
Carol, you're really getting into this.

351
00:23:40,932 --> 00:23:45,608
I know. My therapist suggested it
as a way to get over my little blip.

352
00:23:46,572 --> 00:23:50,326
I think it's really working.
I feel terrific, especially tonight.

353
00:23:50,532 --> 00:23:53,410
I am so happy for you guys!

354
00:23:53,772 --> 00:23:55,046
Excuse me.

355
00:23:58,012 --> 00:24:00,242
Bad breakup. Long story.

356
00:24:01,012 --> 00:24:03,924
Let's go say hello to Uncle Vito. Come on.

357
00:24:04,612 --> 00:24:05,931
Here we go.

358
00:24:16,732 --> 00:24:18,404
Hey, Uncle Vito!

359
00:24:20,332 --> 00:24:22,323
Don't you look beautiful!

360
00:24:25,212 --> 00:24:28,284
Always so beautiful. You're like a flower.

361
00:24:28,492 --> 00:24:30,164
Well, you too, Uncle Vito.

362
00:24:30,572 --> 00:24:33,086
This is so nice.
We planned something much smaller.

363
00:24:33,172 --> 00:24:34,400
Yes, thank you.

364
00:24:36,412 --> 00:24:37,845
Your school....

365
00:24:38,172 --> 00:24:39,446
How is everything?

366
00:24:39,532 --> 00:24:43,207
It's pretty good.
Only two shootings last week.

367
00:24:43,412 --> 00:24:45,164
It's got me sick with worry.

368
00:24:45,252 --> 00:24:47,368
Why do you want to worry your father?

369
00:24:47,572 --> 00:24:51,406
You want to transfer? I have a friend
of a friend in the supervisor's office.

370
00:24:51,492 --> 00:24:53,528
Thank you. I'll let you know.

371
00:24:59,692 --> 00:25:02,047
Are your family coming over
for the wedding?

372
00:25:02,172 --> 00:25:02,968
No.

373
00:25:03,092 --> 00:25:04,161
Michael's an orphan.

374
00:25:04,252 --> 00:25:05,321
He was.

375
00:25:07,452 --> 00:25:09,124
I'm sorry to hear that.

376
00:25:09,932 --> 00:25:13,049
Tell me, Michael, I'm interested to know...

377
00:25:13,372 --> 00:25:15,488
...coming from a foreign culture...

378
00:25:15,692 --> 00:25:19,128
...you must have a different perspective
on all these killings.

379
00:25:26,932 --> 00:25:30,811
To speak honestly,
I can't say I really approve...

380
00:25:31,012 --> 00:25:34,129
...but my understanding is
that it's all part of your business...

381
00:25:34,212 --> 00:25:38,649
...and that people only get killed
who bring it on themselves.

382
00:25:42,292 --> 00:25:44,408
The killings at Gina's high school.

383
00:25:48,732 --> 00:25:50,165
I'm against them.

384
00:25:53,532 --> 00:25:56,524
What do you say we show him
around the house a little?

385
00:26:02,532 --> 00:26:05,888
$250,000. You think it's worth that?

386
00:26:06,332 --> 00:26:08,971
Like I say, that's the great thing
about an auction.

387
00:26:09,052 --> 00:26:12,442
An object is worth
whatever anyone is willing to pay for it.

388
00:26:12,932 --> 00:26:15,127
That's an interesting perspective.

389
00:26:17,572 --> 00:26:19,688
Tell me what you think of this one.

390
00:26:23,132 --> 00:26:24,451
You like it?

391
00:26:29,532 --> 00:26:31,011
It's very...

392
00:26:31,612 --> 00:26:33,250
...intriguing, isn't it?

393
00:26:33,332 --> 00:26:35,004
Tell me, why does...

394
00:26:35,532 --> 00:26:37,363
...Jesus have a machine gun?

395
00:26:37,572 --> 00:26:42,327
It's symbolic. You have to ask Johnny.
He does them as part of his therapy.

396
00:26:43,052 --> 00:26:46,283
You have a very gifted son, Vito.
No two ways about it.

397
00:26:46,492 --> 00:26:48,562
Well, I must say, I like the way...

398
00:26:48,812 --> 00:26:52,248
-...the blood oozes out of his cranium.
-I like that.

399
00:26:54,852 --> 00:26:56,888
He's very talented, wouldn't you say?

400
00:26:56,972 --> 00:26:59,361
Yes, I think he certainly has something.

401
00:27:01,772 --> 00:27:03,888
I'm flattered that you like it.

402
00:27:05,172 --> 00:27:07,925
Listen, Michael. We should talk.

403
00:27:08,212 --> 00:27:10,806
I have friends in various fields...

404
00:27:10,972 --> 00:27:14,203
...that would be delighted
to help a friend of mine.

405
00:27:15,852 --> 00:27:19,322
Well, that's extremely kind of you...

406
00:27:20,852 --> 00:27:25,562
...but I've always had this silly thing about
standing on my own two feet in business.

407
00:27:27,332 --> 00:27:30,404
I hope you understand.

408
00:27:36,372 --> 00:27:37,851
Of course.

409
00:27:39,292 --> 00:27:41,203
I respect your feeling.

410
00:27:53,692 --> 00:27:55,330
"You're nobody...

411
00:27:56,412 --> 00:27:59,165
"...till somebody loves you"

412
00:28:01,852 --> 00:28:03,604
I'm so proud of you.

413
00:28:03,932 --> 00:28:06,765
-No. You see, I am so proud of you.
-No, you.

414
00:28:06,972 --> 00:28:08,564
-No, you.
-Oh, shut up!

415
00:28:08,652 --> 00:28:09,801
All right.

416
00:28:11,492 --> 00:28:12,481
Perfect!

417
00:28:13,572 --> 00:28:16,086
I am so happy for you.

418
00:28:16,852 --> 00:28:18,331
One more!

419
00:28:20,412 --> 00:28:23,324
"Somebody to love. "

420
00:28:38,412 --> 00:28:41,324
Talk to Helen about tonight's catalog.

421
00:28:41,692 --> 00:28:44,445
Rent GoodFellas, Casino,
Godfa ther l, ll, Ill....

422
00:28:46,852 --> 00:28:49,605
Excuse me. Can I help you?

423
00:28:50,972 --> 00:28:53,042
How much is this one?

424
00:28:53,852 --> 00:28:56,889
On this, the reserve is $30,000, I think.

425
00:28:58,972 --> 00:29:02,282
That being, of course,
the opening bid on tonight's auction.

426
00:29:03,612 --> 00:29:06,410
Do you have much experience
when it comes to buying art?

427
00:29:06,492 --> 00:29:07,561
No.

428
00:29:07,772 --> 00:29:10,844
But I hear it can be a good investment.

429
00:29:11,612 --> 00:29:12,522
Yes.

430
00:29:12,652 --> 00:29:14,324
My father...

431
00:29:14,492 --> 00:29:16,289
...recently died...

432
00:29:18,052 --> 00:29:19,883
...and left me some money.

433
00:29:20,092 --> 00:29:21,241
Your father?

434
00:29:21,372 --> 00:29:23,602
That must've been a terrible shock.

435
00:29:24,612 --> 00:29:27,922
If you're looking for something beautiful
to put on your wall...

436
00:29:28,012 --> 00:29:30,480
...you might like to think about a mirror.

437
00:29:34,452 --> 00:29:35,726
Oh, you!

438
00:29:35,972 --> 00:29:38,532
I really want a painting.

439
00:29:40,212 --> 00:29:42,168
-Can I have a word?
-One moment.

440
00:29:42,492 --> 00:29:47,088
Tonight, if there's a nice painting
going for less than it's really worth...

441
00:29:47,292 --> 00:29:50,170
...perhaps I could let you know about it.

442
00:29:50,372 --> 00:29:52,249
You mean like a signal?

443
00:29:52,412 --> 00:29:53,527
Exactly.

444
00:29:53,732 --> 00:29:56,769
I have an important potential client
I have to talk to.

445
00:29:56,892 --> 00:30:00,328
I'll leave Helen here to work out
the exact details of this with you.

446
00:30:00,412 --> 00:30:02,164
-Where is he?
-Not here yet.

447
00:30:02,492 --> 00:30:04,289
But the trucks are.

448
00:30:04,652 --> 00:30:06,210
That means they're early.

449
00:30:06,292 --> 00:30:07,611
Incredible, huh?

450
00:30:08,252 --> 00:30:09,605
Fantastic!

451
00:30:12,572 --> 00:30:13,607
Hello.

452
00:30:14,052 --> 00:30:14,928
What?

453
00:30:21,212 --> 00:30:24,124
-So that's everything.
-Yes, sir. All 44 pieces.

454
00:30:24,852 --> 00:30:27,366
I just want you to know,
if I've said anything...

455
00:30:27,452 --> 00:30:30,888
...or done anything in the past
that in any way offended you...

456
00:30:31,612 --> 00:30:33,284
...l'm very deeply sorry.

457
00:30:36,532 --> 00:30:37,681
Thanks.

458
00:30:48,852 --> 00:30:50,331
-Are you okay?
-Sorry.

459
00:30:50,412 --> 00:30:53,051
Yes, I'm fine. I was just....

460
00:30:53,732 --> 00:30:57,122
The delivery was complete and on time.
It was a bit of a shock.

461
00:30:57,212 --> 00:30:58,327
I can imagine.

462
00:30:58,412 --> 00:31:00,004
Morganson's here.

463
00:31:00,212 --> 00:31:04,091
I thought you could soften him up a bit,
then I'll move in for the kill.

464
00:31:04,732 --> 00:31:05,767
Absolutely.

465
00:31:05,852 --> 00:31:06,807
Lovely.

466
00:31:07,492 --> 00:31:09,005
We do like to think we can...

467
00:31:09,092 --> 00:31:12,687
...match Sotheby's in the two qualities
most important to any auction house.

468
00:31:12,772 --> 00:31:16,082
One being, obviously,
a tradition of unquestioned respectability.

469
00:31:16,172 --> 00:31:19,448
And the other being,
for want of a better word...

470
00:31:19,612 --> 00:31:21,921
...shall we say, "class."

471
00:31:29,172 --> 00:31:31,481
I know Mr. Cromwell
is anxious to talk to you.

472
00:31:37,172 --> 00:31:39,640
I'm sorry, I'm confused.
What's the problem?

473
00:31:39,732 --> 00:31:43,202
Mr. Graziosi wants me
to auction it for $50,000.

474
00:31:43,612 --> 00:31:47,400
People would pay $50,000 just to avoid
being in the same room as this thing.

475
00:31:47,492 --> 00:31:48,402
Michael, please.

476
00:31:48,492 --> 00:31:52,371
Your trucks show up on time
for the first time in God knows how long.

477
00:31:52,572 --> 00:31:55,848
And you get to give a little happiness
to an important friend.

478
00:31:55,932 --> 00:31:58,287
What's the matter?
I thought you'd be happy.

479
00:31:58,372 --> 00:31:59,521
No. Mr. Vitale--

480
00:31:59,612 --> 00:32:00,567
No, Dad.

481
00:32:00,652 --> 00:32:03,928
You don't understand. This is exactly
what Gina said would happen.

482
00:32:04,012 --> 00:32:07,448
If she even found out
that this thing had been sent over here--

483
00:32:08,132 --> 00:32:09,326
You're early.

484
00:32:09,572 --> 00:32:11,130
Just on the phone with your dad.

485
00:32:11,212 --> 00:32:12,531
Let me talk.

486
00:32:16,612 --> 00:32:17,931
You got my message?

487
00:32:18,012 --> 00:32:20,480
Great. And everything's okay
for tomorrow?

488
00:32:21,252 --> 00:32:23,846
And tomorrow at noon
is okay for the fittings?

489
00:32:24,252 --> 00:32:26,812
Well, here's the deal. I'm gonna be there...

490
00:32:27,012 --> 00:32:30,084
...and Carol's gonna come along too,
to take photos.

491
00:32:30,692 --> 00:32:33,160
She's doing the whole wedding, so be nice.

492
00:32:34,532 --> 00:32:37,046
We have to talk
about the wedding reception.

493
00:32:38,812 --> 00:32:41,326
Now, I know you and Mom used Louie's--

494
00:32:43,932 --> 00:32:44,887
Hold on.

495
00:32:50,172 --> 00:32:54,404
We have two key attributes for which,
in this business, there is no substitute.

496
00:32:54,612 --> 00:32:58,400
The first being, obviously,
a tradition of unparalleled respectability.

497
00:32:58,492 --> 00:33:01,882
And the other being, shall we say,
for want of a better word--

498
00:33:05,932 --> 00:33:07,490
We'll come back later.

499
00:33:09,412 --> 00:33:11,289
Right. Fine.

500
00:33:11,572 --> 00:33:13,164
Daddy, we have to go.

501
00:33:13,372 --> 00:33:14,600
I love you too.

502
00:33:16,092 --> 00:33:17,605
He wants to say 'bye.

503
00:33:20,572 --> 00:33:22,164
It's gonna be okay.

504
00:33:22,332 --> 00:33:26,120
You put the thing up for auction.
It don't sell, Gina will never know.

505
00:33:26,332 --> 00:33:28,129
I don't think I can do that.

506
00:33:30,012 --> 00:33:34,483
Listen, this favor....
If you don't do it, it's really not that great.

507
00:33:34,692 --> 00:33:37,286
Not for you, and to be honest with you,
not for me.

508
00:33:37,372 --> 00:33:40,125
So just do it this once,
and I'll talk to Vito...

509
00:33:40,212 --> 00:33:44,603
...and explain how in the future
you two would prefer to go it alone, okay?

510
00:33:45,852 --> 00:33:47,251
Is that a promise, Dad?

511
00:33:47,332 --> 00:33:48,685
That's a promise.

512
00:33:50,932 --> 00:33:54,288
Fabulous. Noon tomorrow then it is.
Okay, 'bye.

513
00:33:55,332 --> 00:33:56,924
What is wrong with you?

514
00:33:58,012 --> 00:33:59,650
You, come here!

515
00:34:05,372 --> 00:34:08,330
I swear to God, Frankie,
I ain't got the money!

516
00:34:09,092 --> 00:34:11,560
Now I gotta put you on mountain climb.

517
00:34:25,172 --> 00:34:27,288
-We worked out the signals.
-What?

518
00:34:27,572 --> 00:34:29,085
With the old lady.

519
00:34:29,532 --> 00:34:31,807
If you want her to start bidding, you cough.

520
00:34:31,892 --> 00:34:32,802
Easy enough.

521
00:34:32,892 --> 00:34:35,884
If you want her to stop bidding,
you just say "ha."

522
00:34:36,092 --> 00:34:38,765
Fine. What? Say what?

523
00:34:39,212 --> 00:34:40,201
Ha!

524
00:34:45,092 --> 00:34:46,889
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

525
00:34:46,972 --> 00:34:49,964
And welcome to
"Portraiture: 1450 to 1750. "

526
00:34:59,812 --> 00:35:01,450
And down it goes, then...

527
00:35:01,532 --> 00:35:04,968
...at $25,000 to bidder number 977.

528
00:35:06,452 --> 00:35:09,171
And so to our final piece of the evening...

529
00:35:10,012 --> 00:35:13,641
...and a last-minute addition
to your catalog...

530
00:35:13,852 --> 00:35:16,412
...lot number 277A...

531
00:35:16,612 --> 00:35:19,763
...oil on canvas, signed by the artist:

532
00:35:20,092 --> 00:35:23,880
The Road To Damascus
by Jonathan Graziosi.

533
00:35:25,452 --> 00:35:26,646
This item...

534
00:35:26,732 --> 00:35:30,122
...has a reserve of $50,000.
$50,000, anyone?

535
00:35:30,812 --> 00:35:31,642
No.

536
00:35:31,732 --> 00:35:34,166
Well, too bad. Thank you very much.

537
00:35:34,452 --> 00:35:36,522
That concludes the business for--

538
00:35:38,172 --> 00:35:39,287
Was that....

539
00:35:43,252 --> 00:35:45,482
We have $50,000.

540
00:35:46,612 --> 00:35:49,001
$50,000.

541
00:35:50,252 --> 00:35:51,651
$55,000, anyone?

542
00:35:53,252 --> 00:35:55,402
All through. All done, then...

543
00:35:55,612 --> 00:35:59,127
...at $50,000 to bidder number 235.

544
00:36:00,412 --> 00:36:02,687
I believe that's a record for a Graziosi.

545
00:36:02,772 --> 00:36:06,401
Thank you very much,
ladies and gentlemen, and good night.

546
00:36:13,052 --> 00:36:16,249
You snuck that last one in on me,
didn't you?

547
00:36:16,412 --> 00:36:18,368
Yes, I'm afraid so. I'm sorry.

548
00:36:18,452 --> 00:36:20,090
Do that more often.

549
00:36:20,412 --> 00:36:23,768
Congratulations. Quite a painting
you have for yourself, sir.

550
00:36:24,092 --> 00:36:25,810
Thank you. I appreciate that.

551
00:36:25,892 --> 00:36:28,725
I'm sorry. Have we met somewhere?

552
00:36:29,052 --> 00:36:30,451
I don't believe so.

553
00:36:30,772 --> 00:36:33,286
But may I ask,
do either of you enjoy steak?

554
00:36:33,452 --> 00:36:34,805
Very much so.

555
00:36:35,292 --> 00:36:38,011
University and 9th. I'm very proud of it.

556
00:36:45,252 --> 00:36:48,608
You make me very proud
and Johnny very happy.

557
00:36:50,052 --> 00:36:52,043
There's something going on here!

558
00:36:52,812 --> 00:36:55,372
-Nothing's going on.
-I don't like your face.

559
00:37:01,972 --> 00:37:04,645
Frank? I've been trying
to get you since last night.

560
00:37:04,732 --> 00:37:08,281
Listen, it sold. Did you know
that the painting actually sold?

561
00:37:08,492 --> 00:37:10,562
Right on. I heard. That's great.

562
00:37:10,892 --> 00:37:13,281
Did you talk to your friend?

563
00:37:13,492 --> 00:37:16,006
That is it, right? Finito, no more favors.

564
00:37:16,212 --> 00:37:17,440
Trust me, Michael.

565
00:37:17,532 --> 00:37:19,488
-It's gonna be okay.
-Great.

566
00:37:19,692 --> 00:37:23,162
Wait. Wait. Sorry.
It is, or it's going to be?

567
00:37:23,292 --> 00:37:24,645
Hello?

568
00:37:24,732 --> 00:37:27,121
Sorry, gotta go. See you at the tailor.

569
00:37:33,212 --> 00:37:35,806
Excuse me. What's going on?

570
00:37:36,012 --> 00:37:37,889
Big fire over on 72nd Street.

571
00:37:38,172 --> 00:37:39,525
A restaurant or something?

572
00:37:39,612 --> 00:37:40,840
Some art place.

573
00:37:43,492 --> 00:37:44,561
Sotheby's?

574
00:37:45,052 --> 00:37:46,087
That's it.

575
00:38:18,132 --> 00:38:20,851
There are some men here
to see you from the FBl.

576
00:38:23,932 --> 00:38:24,887
Good.

577
00:38:25,692 --> 00:38:26,807
Good, good.

578
00:38:30,532 --> 00:38:32,523
We often sell works by first-time artists.

579
00:38:32,612 --> 00:38:34,842
I don't see how this time is any different.

580
00:38:34,932 --> 00:38:38,083
The difference is this painting was bought
by a restaurant owner...

581
00:38:38,292 --> 00:38:40,886
...who owed the artist's father $50,000.

582
00:38:41,452 --> 00:38:44,125
It's a setup.
They bought it from themselves.

583
00:38:44,412 --> 00:38:48,485
I don't understand. Someone buys your
painting for $50,000, you make $50,000.

584
00:38:48,692 --> 00:38:51,001
But if they owed you the money,
you make nothing.

585
00:38:51,092 --> 00:38:52,969
It's called money laundering.

586
00:38:54,492 --> 00:38:55,527
You mind?

587
00:38:55,932 --> 00:38:57,160
Not at all, no.

588
00:38:58,652 --> 00:39:01,166
They do it through car washes,
restaurants...

589
00:39:01,252 --> 00:39:03,766
...bars and, last night, through you.

590
00:39:04,252 --> 00:39:06,482
Have you at any time come into contact...

591
00:39:06,652 --> 00:39:09,883
...with anyone who might be connected
with organized crime?

592
00:39:13,692 --> 00:39:14,920
Absolutely not.

593
00:39:16,492 --> 00:39:17,971
You sure about that?

594
00:39:19,132 --> 00:39:20,611
I am positive.

595
00:39:40,452 --> 00:39:42,090
Are we okay to see Michael?

596
00:39:42,172 --> 00:39:44,402
He's in with the FBl.

597
00:39:45,692 --> 00:39:46,727
Lovely.

598
00:39:47,572 --> 00:39:49,051
Perhaps later, then.

599
00:39:49,492 --> 00:39:50,925
Have you had lunch?

600
00:39:55,772 --> 00:39:57,763
Thank you very much for the warning.

601
00:39:57,852 --> 00:40:01,208
If anything like this crops up again,
I'll certainly be in touch.

602
00:40:01,292 --> 00:40:02,850
We'd appreciate that.

603
00:40:02,932 --> 00:40:05,571
We're dealing with something
pretty ugly here.

604
00:40:06,132 --> 00:40:07,645
Here's my card.

605
00:40:08,572 --> 00:40:09,448
Thank you.

606
00:40:09,532 --> 00:40:11,170
Oh, those. Thank you.

607
00:40:15,012 --> 00:40:16,525
Gina is in reception.

608
00:40:16,972 --> 00:40:18,325
Good. Thank you.

609
00:40:20,012 --> 00:40:22,651
I know what you're thinking.
It's okay. Relax.

610
00:40:23,372 --> 00:40:24,725
Mr. Felgate.

611
00:40:24,932 --> 00:40:26,570
Where did you want this?

612
00:40:31,292 --> 00:40:33,806
In my office. Thank you. Quick as you can.

613
00:40:41,732 --> 00:40:45,361
Vito and Johnny are taking more
of a liking to the idea...

614
00:40:45,572 --> 00:40:48,530
...than any of us had perhaps
originally anticipated.

615
00:40:48,612 --> 00:40:51,570
My God! It's out of control!
You can't control it!

616
00:40:51,772 --> 00:40:54,161
Listen now. It is not out of control.

617
00:40:54,532 --> 00:40:56,170
I have to tell Gina.

618
00:40:56,772 --> 00:40:59,730
Tonight is your last auction
of the season, right?

619
00:41:00,092 --> 00:41:01,969
Just keep Gina away from there.

620
00:41:02,052 --> 00:41:03,883
Sell the painting, go on your honeymoon.

621
00:41:03,972 --> 00:41:06,805
When you come back,
everything will be taken care of.

622
00:41:07,012 --> 00:41:09,924
I am not lying to Gina. I have to tell her.

623
00:41:10,132 --> 00:41:11,406
Michael, please.

624
00:41:11,492 --> 00:41:15,610
Gina's happiness means more to me than
anything in the world. You know that.

625
00:41:16,332 --> 00:41:19,529
If you tell her now that you already lied...

626
00:41:19,932 --> 00:41:21,285
...it's all over.

627
00:41:28,412 --> 00:41:30,368
Goddamn it!

628
00:41:32,692 --> 00:41:33,841
This is your fault!

629
00:41:33,932 --> 00:41:37,049
You know, I've been on your side
every step of the way.

630
00:41:37,252 --> 00:41:40,562
If you were a plumber,
would we be having this conversation?

631
00:41:45,532 --> 00:41:48,524
Look at you!

632
00:41:48,732 --> 00:41:50,370
Wait. Where's Ritchie?

633
00:41:54,332 --> 00:41:55,287
Smile!

634
00:41:57,452 --> 00:41:58,885
What's the matter with you?

635
00:41:58,972 --> 00:42:00,166
I don't know.

636
00:42:00,452 --> 00:42:02,920
So, are you guys busy tonight?

637
00:42:03,292 --> 00:42:06,841
Actually, I'm gonna go to Michael's
big auction. You wanna come?

638
00:42:07,372 --> 00:42:08,327
Yes.

639
00:42:09,092 --> 00:42:10,810
We should talk about that.

640
00:42:11,092 --> 00:42:11,968
What?

641
00:42:12,092 --> 00:42:16,085
Tonight. I've been thinking about it.
You know, it's quite a big deal.

642
00:42:16,292 --> 00:42:18,681
Morganson's gonna be there again...

643
00:42:19,652 --> 00:42:23,008
...and I'm just afraid I might get put off
if you were there.

644
00:42:23,412 --> 00:42:25,528
I know it sounds silly.

645
00:42:25,692 --> 00:42:29,731
I just might not be able to see the bids
because I'd, you know...

646
00:42:30,812 --> 00:42:33,246
...not be able to look at you.

647
00:42:35,652 --> 00:42:37,608
What? What is it?

648
00:42:37,972 --> 00:42:39,405
What is it?

649
00:42:39,932 --> 00:42:41,524
I'm fine.

650
00:42:42,492 --> 00:42:43,720
Just, he....

651
00:42:45,212 --> 00:42:49,649
He loves you so much,
and I am so happy for you.

652
00:42:53,852 --> 00:42:57,447
No, it's so great.

653
00:42:59,412 --> 00:43:01,243
It's so good.

654
00:43:17,692 --> 00:43:21,082
And so, finally, to lot 125A.

655
00:43:21,412 --> 00:43:24,609
And another of our occasional
Jonathan Graziosi's.

656
00:43:25,132 --> 00:43:27,771
This unusual painting is entitled:

657
00:43:27,932 --> 00:43:29,604
Die, Piggy-Piggy, Die, Die...

658
00:43:29,692 --> 00:43:32,047
...and has a reserve of $80,000.

659
00:43:33,132 --> 00:43:35,248
At $80,000, then.

660
00:43:37,492 --> 00:43:38,447
Anyone?

661
00:43:40,412 --> 00:43:41,640
Bid.

662
00:43:41,852 --> 00:43:43,251
$80,000.

663
00:43:51,612 --> 00:43:52,681
Excuse me.

664
00:43:55,932 --> 00:43:57,047
Is that...?

665
00:43:58,772 --> 00:43:59,841
We have...

666
00:44:00,772 --> 00:44:03,127
...$80,000, lady at the front.

667
00:44:04,972 --> 00:44:06,690
$85,000, anyone?

668
00:44:09,532 --> 00:44:13,730
$85,000, gentleman at the back.
No advance. No one else. All through--

669
00:44:15,612 --> 00:44:17,887
$90,000.

670
00:44:18,852 --> 00:44:20,285
$90,000.

671
00:44:21,132 --> 00:44:22,121
Ha!

672
00:44:22,412 --> 00:44:24,323
Anyone at $95,000?

673
00:44:24,532 --> 00:44:26,762
Be smart, take her money.
Let me pay you later!

674
00:44:26,852 --> 00:44:29,002
You're supposed to buy the painting.

675
00:44:29,132 --> 00:44:32,169
-But you can make double the money!
-Just doing my job.

676
00:44:32,252 --> 00:44:34,322
Yes, $95,000. Ha!

677
00:44:36,732 --> 00:44:38,927
$100,000.

678
00:44:39,532 --> 00:44:41,727
Anyone at $105,000?

679
00:44:43,492 --> 00:44:46,006
$105,000, gentleman at the back.

680
00:44:46,172 --> 00:44:48,732
May I remind you,
we recently sold a Graziosi...

681
00:44:48,812 --> 00:44:52,088
...for a record $50,000,
the most ever paid for a Graziosi.

682
00:44:52,732 --> 00:44:56,247
$50,000, less than, ha, half
the current bidding price.

683
00:44:59,292 --> 00:45:00,964
$110,000.

684
00:45:01,172 --> 00:45:03,208
Anyone at $115?

685
00:45:05,572 --> 00:45:06,607
Sir?

686
00:45:07,652 --> 00:45:08,687
$115?

687
00:45:09,012 --> 00:45:10,365
I told you.

688
00:45:11,412 --> 00:45:15,769
Certainly, to let this go for $110,000 would
be a crime of the greatest magnitude.

689
00:45:20,332 --> 00:45:22,641
Yes! $115,000, gentleman at the back.

690
00:45:22,852 --> 00:45:26,162
All done, and down it goes at $115,000
to bidder number 702.

691
00:45:26,372 --> 00:45:30,331
That brings us to the end of the auction.
Thank you. Good night.

692
00:45:34,212 --> 00:45:36,282
I can't talk. I have to see Gina.

693
00:45:44,812 --> 00:45:47,849
Gina told me the happy news.
I'm baking you two a cake.

694
00:45:49,092 --> 00:45:50,764
That's incredibly nice of you.

695
00:45:50,852 --> 00:45:52,808
I'll see you a bit later, then.

696
00:46:13,692 --> 00:46:15,444
Who are you? What is this?

697
00:46:15,612 --> 00:46:18,809
It's the three-month anniversary
of our very first date.

698
00:46:19,132 --> 00:46:20,770
I'm a complete...

699
00:46:21,372 --> 00:46:22,725
...idiot. Sorry.

700
00:46:22,972 --> 00:46:24,610
But do you mind company?

701
00:46:24,772 --> 00:46:25,568
Who?

702
00:46:29,812 --> 00:46:32,280
Humans and gorillas are primates.

703
00:46:32,492 --> 00:46:34,528
-He reminded me of you.
-He would.

704
00:46:34,612 --> 00:46:36,364
Happy anniversary.

705
00:46:37,372 --> 00:46:41,411
My God. I feel so horrible that
I didn't remember to get anything for you.

706
00:46:43,012 --> 00:46:44,365
Oh, my God!

707
00:46:45,412 --> 00:46:46,322
Swap?

708
00:46:47,012 --> 00:46:49,048
You can't afford this!

709
00:46:50,612 --> 00:46:51,806
Come here.

710
00:46:54,772 --> 00:46:56,842
I have an opposable thumb.

711
00:46:57,052 --> 00:46:58,246
Gina, hang on.

712
00:46:58,332 --> 00:47:00,288
Calm down. Calm down.

713
00:47:00,492 --> 00:47:03,245
Listen, I can afford it, because, you know...

714
00:47:03,452 --> 00:47:06,569
...things have been going really well
at work recently.

715
00:47:06,772 --> 00:47:07,966
Apart from...

716
00:47:11,492 --> 00:47:15,804
...this one thing that I think
we should talk about, okay?

717
00:47:22,772 --> 00:47:24,046
I'll go.

718
00:47:31,292 --> 00:47:32,361
Who is it?

719
00:47:34,532 --> 00:47:37,444
It's Jehovah bloody Witnesses.

720
00:47:37,732 --> 00:47:40,485
Please go away. Thank you.
We're not interested.

721
00:47:42,612 --> 00:47:44,330
They must be very devoted.

722
00:47:44,492 --> 00:47:45,447
Hang on.

723
00:47:45,532 --> 00:47:46,601
Excuse me.

724
00:47:46,932 --> 00:47:49,048
I want my money now.

725
00:47:49,252 --> 00:47:53,404
-I can't talk about this now.
-No talk. Money. Now!

726
00:47:55,332 --> 00:47:56,242
Hello, Gina.

727
00:47:56,692 --> 00:47:58,364
Michael, what's going on?

728
00:47:58,572 --> 00:48:01,848
Prince Charles here just cost me $130,000.

729
00:48:02,052 --> 00:48:05,601
And he's gonna make it up
out of his own pocket. What's this worth?

730
00:48:05,692 --> 00:48:08,490
They were auctioning Johnny's paintings
to launder money.

731
00:48:08,572 --> 00:48:09,607
Not "they."

732
00:48:09,692 --> 00:48:10,568
"We."

733
00:48:10,772 --> 00:48:13,969
And a connoisseur had the taste
to try to buy some of my art.

734
00:48:14,052 --> 00:48:16,725
She was 90 years old and blind.
She wasn't a connoisseur.

735
00:48:16,812 --> 00:48:19,610
Your jerk fiancé wouldn't even let her bid.

736
00:48:19,772 --> 00:48:22,286
Cheating innocent collectors
wasn't part of the deal!

737
00:48:22,372 --> 00:48:23,600
You had a deal?

738
00:48:24,092 --> 00:48:25,002
No. No.

739
00:48:25,092 --> 00:48:27,481
When angered, I make this sound....

740
00:48:27,972 --> 00:48:31,601
Then how come you took commission
from the painting I sold last night?

741
00:48:31,692 --> 00:48:33,922
This is why you told me
not to come tonight.

742
00:48:34,012 --> 00:48:36,924
Because if I was there,
you'd have trouble not looking at me.

743
00:48:37,012 --> 00:48:38,730
Very smooth. Very smooth.

744
00:48:38,812 --> 00:48:41,485
Did you take a commission?
ls that how you afforded this?

745
00:48:41,572 --> 00:48:44,166
We burst your little
Town & Country bubble here?

746
00:48:44,252 --> 00:48:45,924
I don't know who you think you are--

747
00:48:46,012 --> 00:48:47,968
-That's it! Get out.
-Don't touch me!

748
00:48:48,052 --> 00:48:49,610
All right. All right.

749
00:48:49,692 --> 00:48:51,683
Other primates fear the gorilla.

750
00:48:51,812 --> 00:48:53,530
Don't be a moron, Johnny.

751
00:48:53,892 --> 00:48:56,770
Just relax, okay? Relax.

752
00:48:57,052 --> 00:48:59,612
Come on, Johnny. You don't need the gun.

753
00:49:00,412 --> 00:49:02,050
You're right. I don't.

754
00:49:05,932 --> 00:49:08,810
I hate to do this
to such a beautiful establishment...

755
00:49:08,892 --> 00:49:11,122
...but you gotta learn how to pay up!

756
00:49:12,252 --> 00:49:13,128
Stop.

757
00:49:14,532 --> 00:49:15,567
Stop!

758
00:49:21,492 --> 00:49:24,086
My diet is leaves and fresh fruit.

759
00:49:24,572 --> 00:49:25,687
Oh, my God!

760
00:49:26,012 --> 00:49:28,401
What happened? Did it ricochet?

761
00:49:31,772 --> 00:49:32,887
He's dead.

762
00:49:35,572 --> 00:49:38,405
Oh, my God! Oh, my God....

763
00:49:39,652 --> 00:49:41,608
It's not your fault. It's okay.

764
00:49:41,692 --> 00:49:44,604
Here's what we'll do.
I'm gonna call the police.

765
00:49:45,412 --> 00:49:46,925
You can't.

766
00:49:47,132 --> 00:49:49,168
They own half the police.

767
00:49:50,252 --> 00:49:51,287
What have I done?

768
00:49:51,372 --> 00:49:52,691
Don't you worry.

769
00:49:52,972 --> 00:49:55,532
-You go home. I'll call your father.
-Daddy?

770
00:49:55,612 --> 00:49:57,170
We can deal with this.

