936
01:01:28,003 --> 01:01:30,801
-You thought that was to strangle her?
-What else?

937
01:01:30,883 --> 01:01:35,195
Tie her up so I could take her to my cabin.
I mean, my God!

938
01:01:35,403 --> 01:01:37,155
What kind of person do you think I am?

939
01:01:37,243 --> 01:01:40,792
The kind of person who knows the trick
for carrying a dead body.

940
01:01:42,083 --> 01:01:43,198
Oh, my God!

941
01:01:43,963 --> 01:01:45,396
Hey, get outta here.

942
01:01:45,603 --> 01:01:47,719
-No, just forget about it.
-"Forget about it."

943
01:01:47,803 --> 01:01:49,714
No, I mean, shut up.

944
01:01:49,923 --> 01:01:52,153
Please, shut up!

945
01:01:52,443 --> 01:01:53,637
"Forget about it."

946
01:02:15,163 --> 01:02:18,280
My God! I sold him the painting.
He knows who I am.

947
01:02:19,003 --> 01:02:20,641
This can't be happening.

948
01:02:22,523 --> 01:02:24,400
You gentlemen ready to order?

949
01:02:25,243 --> 01:02:29,316
Just a salad and some mineral water.
I'm counting my cholesterol.

950
01:02:30,123 --> 01:02:34,196
I'll have a sirloin, medium, fried onions,
baked potato with everything on it.

951
01:02:34,843 --> 01:02:35,958
And a beer.

952
01:02:36,123 --> 01:02:37,112
Same.

953
01:02:37,923 --> 01:02:39,038
And you?

954
01:02:39,483 --> 01:02:40,313
Same.

955
01:02:40,603 --> 01:02:42,559
How you want your steak cooked?

956
01:02:47,203 --> 01:02:48,477
Rare.

957
01:02:48,683 --> 01:02:49,718
What?

958
01:02:50,523 --> 01:02:51,512
Raw.

959
01:02:51,803 --> 01:02:52,758
What?

960
01:02:52,963 --> 01:02:53,759
Raw!

961
01:02:53,923 --> 01:02:54,912
Raw?

962
01:02:56,923 --> 01:02:57,878
Rare?

963
01:02:58,243 --> 01:02:59,358
Rare.

964
01:03:03,323 --> 01:03:04,915
And how about to drink?

965
01:03:06,363 --> 01:03:07,273
Beer.

966
01:03:07,483 --> 01:03:08,916
Another beer.

967
01:03:09,883 --> 01:03:11,316
You talk funny.

968
01:03:13,883 --> 01:03:16,272
You got any company
while you're in town?

969
01:03:19,163 --> 01:03:20,482
Hey, Antoinette!

970
01:03:20,763 --> 01:03:21,832
Come here.

971
01:03:25,283 --> 01:03:26,955
This here's a good friend of ours.

972
01:03:27,043 --> 01:03:28,920
Kansas City Little Big Mickey Blue Eyes.

973
01:03:29,003 --> 01:03:30,755
Well, that's a mouthful.

974
01:03:31,243 --> 01:03:33,473
Sit down. Say hi to the nice man.

975
01:03:36,083 --> 01:03:37,072
Hi.

976
01:03:38,563 --> 01:03:41,919
Mickey Blue Eyes.
Why do they call you that?

977
01:03:44,603 --> 01:03:46,719
So what part of Kansas City?

978
01:03:50,363 --> 01:03:53,082
-Are they taking care of you?
-Get back in your kitchen!

979
01:03:53,163 --> 01:03:54,915
I want something, I'll ask!

980
01:04:02,843 --> 01:04:04,674
Kansas City, here I come.

981
01:04:05,723 --> 01:04:08,442
Rent GoodFellas, Casino,
Godfather l, ll, Ill....

982
01:04:08,523 --> 01:04:10,161
Jesus Christ, it talks?

983
01:04:10,243 --> 01:04:12,074
With an accent, no less.

984
01:04:12,283 --> 01:04:13,477
What is that?

985
01:04:13,563 --> 01:04:17,272
It's like a little recorder thing.
Got it off some British asshole.

986
01:04:18,043 --> 01:04:19,874
What an amazing coincidence.

987
01:04:20,643 --> 01:04:22,998
Come for one of the famous steaks?

988
01:04:24,603 --> 01:04:26,434
Is something queer going on?

989
01:04:27,083 --> 01:04:30,041
Is this in any way connected
to that FBI business?

990
01:04:30,283 --> 01:04:33,241
Philip, I can't explain at the moment.

991
01:04:33,563 --> 01:04:35,872
What was going on
at the auction last night?

992
01:04:35,963 --> 01:04:39,160
Why did you keep saying "ha"?
We were worried about you.

993
01:04:39,683 --> 01:04:41,401
I'll have to explain later.

994
01:04:43,363 --> 01:04:44,682
Oh, my God! I am so sorry.

995
01:04:44,883 --> 01:04:46,111
This is all my fault.

996
01:04:46,363 --> 01:04:48,081
I can't apologize enough--

997
01:04:49,883 --> 01:04:52,477
Just a little screwup. But what the hell?

998
01:04:52,763 --> 01:04:54,355
We got it under control.

999
01:04:54,563 --> 01:04:55,916
Forget about it.

1000
01:04:56,603 --> 01:04:57,638
Why are you talking--

1001
01:04:57,723 --> 01:05:00,157
Shut up, asshole! I had enough a you!

1002
01:05:00,323 --> 01:05:02,791
I said shut up! Get outta here!

1003
01:05:03,003 --> 01:05:04,561
All you British are the same!

1004
01:05:04,643 --> 01:05:07,157
You're all assholes!
Go on! Get outta here!

1005
01:05:14,323 --> 01:05:15,358
Asshole.

1006
01:05:20,723 --> 01:05:22,998
-What are they doing?
-Talking to Kansas City.

1007
01:05:23,083 --> 01:05:26,075
They can't connect us to Johnny
if I get to the old lady first.

1008
01:05:26,163 --> 01:05:30,395
But she spends her afternoons
playing cards and comes home about 3:00.

1009
01:05:32,283 --> 01:05:34,353
What? What?

1010
01:05:35,203 --> 01:05:37,034
I missed meeting Gina for lunch.

1011
01:05:37,123 --> 01:05:40,399
Give her a call. Explain what happened.
It'll be okay.

1012
01:05:40,643 --> 01:05:43,077
Just wake up, Frank. It will not be okay!

1013
01:05:43,163 --> 01:05:47,361
I assaulted my boss, lost my fiancée,
and your pals are going to kill me!

1014
01:05:47,763 --> 01:05:51,358
Of all the things it won't be,
"okay" pretty much tops the list.

1015
01:05:51,563 --> 01:05:53,076
You have to stay focused.

1016
01:05:53,163 --> 01:05:56,200
Focus on this. Gina won't forgive me.
Do you know why?

1017
01:05:56,443 --> 01:06:00,834
I lied to her. Her father's lied
to her all her life. And it hurts.

1018
01:06:02,923 --> 01:06:04,322
She told you that?

1019
01:06:04,483 --> 01:06:08,840
Yeah, and now it looks like I've lost
the only girl I've ever really loved.

1020
01:06:09,043 --> 01:06:12,274
As far as I'm concerned,
it's not bloody "okay" at all.

1021
01:06:18,283 --> 01:06:19,796
You can't go home.

1022
01:06:21,243 --> 01:06:22,596
I'm going to Gina's.

1023
01:06:29,323 --> 01:06:32,042
I should've told you everything
from the start.

1024
01:06:32,283 --> 01:06:35,719
But the whole thing snowballed,
and before I knew where I was...

1025
01:06:35,963 --> 01:06:39,160
...l was just buried in the whole thing.

1026
01:06:39,363 --> 01:06:40,955
But everything I did...

1027
01:06:41,163 --> 01:06:43,233
...l did out of fear of losing you.

1028
01:06:43,963 --> 01:06:47,239
Listen. Please just let me come up.
This is ridiculous.

1029
01:06:47,683 --> 01:06:50,072
Why didn't you show up for lunch today?

1030
01:06:50,523 --> 01:06:51,956
The truth, please.

1031
01:06:52,163 --> 01:06:55,712
I was with your father.
We had to have lunch with these people.

1032
01:06:55,963 --> 01:06:57,078
It was a nightmare.

1033
01:06:57,163 --> 01:07:00,155
It seems like you and Dad
are getting pretty close.

1034
01:07:02,723 --> 01:07:04,202
What does that mean?

1035
01:07:04,643 --> 01:07:08,158
It means we're over, Michael.
I just don't know who you are.

1036
01:07:15,403 --> 01:07:16,916
You're toast.

1037
01:07:25,603 --> 01:07:27,195
-Come here.
-What?

1038
01:07:27,363 --> 01:07:28,716
Don't worry about it.

1039
01:07:28,803 --> 01:07:30,236
It'll be okay.

1040
01:07:32,483 --> 01:07:34,041
Come on!

1041
01:07:34,883 --> 01:07:36,794
Thanks, Jimmy. Thanks.

1042
01:08:09,123 --> 01:08:11,000
She went out, Frankie.

1043
01:08:17,763 --> 01:08:19,515
Michael...

1044
01:08:20,843 --> 01:08:23,403
...fired a warning shot in the ceiling.

1045
01:08:25,083 --> 01:08:26,516
It was an accident.

1046
01:08:27,803 --> 01:08:29,395
Sit down, Frank.

1047
01:08:33,563 --> 01:08:36,282
Having the best time. It's a wonderful city.

1048
01:08:36,483 --> 01:08:40,476
Everyone's so courteous! I don't know
why they talk about New Yorkers--

1049
01:08:40,683 --> 01:08:42,753
Get the hell out of here! Go on!

1050
01:08:51,163 --> 01:08:53,723
Get out of the apartment right now.
Just go.

1051
01:08:55,203 --> 01:08:56,875
What's going on? What's happening?

1052
01:08:56,963 --> 01:08:58,919
Vito thinks the Risollis killed Johnny.

1053
01:08:59,003 --> 01:09:01,312
Things are a little dicey right now.

1054
01:09:01,563 --> 01:09:02,837
I'm fine.

1055
01:09:03,483 --> 01:09:06,714
Vito was worried so he sent Uncle Vinnie
to watch out for me.

1056
01:09:06,803 --> 01:09:08,441
Isn't that sweet of him?

1057
01:09:09,403 --> 01:09:10,358
Daddy?

1058
01:09:11,043 --> 01:09:12,192
You there?

1059
01:09:13,283 --> 01:09:14,682
Okay, listen to me.

1060
01:09:15,323 --> 01:09:18,156
Whatever you do,
I can't explain this right now...

1061
01:09:18,363 --> 01:09:21,719
...but don't tell anyone there's trouble
between you and Michael.

1062
01:09:21,803 --> 01:09:24,522
It's very, very important. You understand?

1063
01:09:26,203 --> 01:09:28,842
-Let me talk to Vinnie.
-Sure, one sec.

1064
01:09:29,083 --> 01:09:30,198
It's Daddy.

1065
01:09:34,043 --> 01:09:36,477
You touch one hair on her head, I swear...

1066
01:09:36,683 --> 01:09:38,002
...you'll beg me to kill you!

1067
01:09:38,083 --> 01:09:41,280
Listen, I'm just doing my job.
All right, Frank?

1068
01:09:41,523 --> 01:09:45,436
You do what you gotta do,
and everything will be okay. All right?

1069
01:09:45,643 --> 01:09:46,712
You--

1070
01:10:21,283 --> 01:10:22,398
So?

1071
01:10:27,643 --> 01:10:29,281
They know what happened.

1072
01:10:31,643 --> 01:10:33,201
They know about Gina?

1073
01:10:35,683 --> 01:10:37,241
They think it was you.

1074
01:10:39,963 --> 01:10:41,442
What's gonna happen?

1075
01:10:42,123 --> 01:10:44,318
They gotta take care of you, Michael.

1076
01:10:45,123 --> 01:10:46,602
What does that mean?

1077
01:10:47,003 --> 01:10:48,356
It means...

1078
01:10:48,603 --> 01:10:50,514
...they ordered someone to....

1079
01:10:52,643 --> 01:10:53,758
Whack me?

1080
01:10:58,163 --> 01:10:59,562
Do we know who?

1081
01:11:01,523 --> 01:11:02,512
Me.

1082
01:11:03,043 --> 01:11:03,998
You?

1083
01:11:05,643 --> 01:11:07,440
You're going to whack me?

1084
01:11:07,643 --> 01:11:10,203
Stop saying that. You sound like an idiot!

1085
01:11:12,283 --> 01:11:16,674
Vito wants me to do it at the wedding,
during your speech.

1086
01:11:17,443 --> 01:11:19,673
That way he figures he gets us both.

1087
01:11:19,883 --> 01:11:24,479
You die, and I lose Gina
by killing the man she loves.

1088
01:11:25,163 --> 01:11:27,279
But there isn't gonna be a wedding.

1089
01:11:28,483 --> 01:11:30,041
So I can't do it then.

1090
01:11:30,883 --> 01:11:33,761
You mean, you can't do it then...

1091
01:11:34,083 --> 01:11:35,755
...or you can't do it, then?

1092
01:11:37,003 --> 01:11:38,402
The first one.

1093
01:11:40,443 --> 01:11:41,398
Right.

1094
01:11:43,083 --> 01:11:46,871
They got Gina. If I don't do it,
Vinnie's gonna kill her.

1095
01:11:47,083 --> 01:11:48,038
My God!

1096
01:11:48,283 --> 01:11:52,196
It's one of these honor things, you know.
A life for a life.

1097
01:11:54,763 --> 01:11:55,991
Bottom line...

1098
01:11:57,403 --> 01:11:59,997
...Vito's not gonna rest
until he sees a body.

1099
01:12:01,763 --> 01:12:03,958
A body. Right.

1100
01:12:23,163 --> 01:12:25,882
This is probably a stupid question, but...

1101
01:12:26,523 --> 01:12:28,753
...to your knowledge, does this hurt?

1102
01:12:30,723 --> 01:12:31,758
No.

1103
01:12:32,603 --> 01:12:34,241
You won't feel a thing.

1104
01:12:34,683 --> 01:12:35,672
Ready?

1105
01:12:36,763 --> 01:12:37,798
Ready.

1106
01:12:45,603 --> 01:12:48,913
That is surprisingly painful.
Is it meant to hurt that much?

1107
01:12:49,083 --> 01:12:50,801
Let me check that for you.

1108
01:12:52,003 --> 01:12:55,234
When Michael gets up
to give his bridegroom speech...

1109
01:12:55,483 --> 01:12:58,555
...you shoot him twice,
then our guys shoot you.

1110
01:12:58,723 --> 01:13:01,874
We'll stitch the squib controls
inside your tuxedos...

1111
01:13:02,083 --> 01:13:06,156
...so you gotta learn to set them off
yourselves, in sync with the gunshots.

1112
01:13:06,243 --> 01:13:07,471
Can you handle it?

1113
01:13:07,563 --> 01:13:09,633
Any problems, speak now.

1114
01:13:10,283 --> 01:13:12,558
This thing is potentially huge for us.

1115
01:13:12,683 --> 01:13:13,877
Massive.

1116
01:13:14,843 --> 01:13:16,879
Questions? Worries?
Something you need?

1117
01:13:16,963 --> 01:13:18,715
Well, just one thing.

1118
01:13:19,563 --> 01:13:20,552
The bride.

1119
01:13:20,643 --> 01:13:22,122
We don't take bribes!

1120
01:13:22,203 --> 01:13:23,431
-Bride!
-Pardon?

1121
01:13:23,643 --> 01:13:25,793
-Bride!
-Take them goddamn things off your head!

1122
01:13:25,883 --> 01:13:26,918
Yes, sir!

1123
01:13:27,403 --> 01:13:29,712
The Handy Bundler
is virtually indestructible!

1124
01:13:29,803 --> 01:13:32,761
Even the law can use Handy Bundler
to detain criminals.

1125
01:13:32,843 --> 01:13:35,915
You'll find hundreds of uses
for the Handy Bundler...

1126
01:13:36,123 --> 01:13:39,354
...at home, in the office and on thejob.

1127
01:13:46,403 --> 01:13:49,156
These guys are doing the flowers
for the wedding?

1128
01:13:49,243 --> 01:13:51,393
Yeah. They're supposed to be great.

1129
01:13:51,483 --> 01:13:54,714
Thanks. I think I'll be safe
with Michael inside.

1130
01:14:15,363 --> 01:14:16,591
What's going on?

1131
01:14:16,683 --> 01:14:19,151
They don't know anything at all about you.

1132
01:14:20,123 --> 01:14:22,591
-They think I shot Johnny.
-But you didn't!

1133
01:14:22,683 --> 01:14:24,275
Act like you're in love.

1134
01:14:25,163 --> 01:14:26,278
Who are you?

1135
01:14:26,363 --> 01:14:29,116
FBl. How are you today?

1136
01:14:29,323 --> 01:14:30,961
Vito doesn't know that I know this...

1137
01:14:31,043 --> 01:14:34,240
...but your father has orders to kill me
at our wedding reception.

1138
01:14:34,323 --> 01:14:36,393
-Michael will be wearing a wire.
-What?

1139
01:14:36,603 --> 01:14:40,915
Vito won't be afraid to talk
because he thinks I'm about to die.

1140
01:14:41,643 --> 01:14:43,122
When he incriminates himself--

1141
01:14:43,203 --> 01:14:45,592
Our guys come in. Bingo! Got him.

1142
01:14:47,803 --> 01:14:49,441
And that's the end of it.

1143
01:14:51,163 --> 01:14:53,358
You think I'd help trap my own father?

1144
01:14:53,443 --> 01:14:55,240
Your father is with us.

1145
01:14:55,883 --> 01:14:58,522
You're more important to him
than they are.

1146
01:14:58,963 --> 01:15:01,079
It's our only way out of this alive.

1147
01:15:04,643 --> 01:15:06,759
Then I guess I don't have a choice.

1148
01:15:07,683 --> 01:15:09,082
Everything okay?

1149
01:15:09,563 --> 01:15:11,997
Everything's fine. Decisions, you know?

1150
01:15:12,803 --> 01:15:14,361
I think we're through.

1151
01:15:15,523 --> 01:15:20,199
Excuse me! Any panics, any questions,
you just give us a call.

1152
01:15:20,443 --> 01:15:23,037
"Tony and Guy, don't be shy."

1153
01:15:23,563 --> 01:15:24,837
'Bye then, darling.

1154
01:15:24,923 --> 01:15:26,197
See you later.

1155
01:15:33,883 --> 01:15:37,193
I can't do this! We have to tell her
Frank will pretend to shoot me.

1156
01:15:37,283 --> 01:15:40,912
No way. Her reaction is everything.
It has to be real.

1157
01:16:07,003 --> 01:16:08,482
Kitchen team moving.

1158
01:16:09,323 --> 01:16:10,995
Bridal limo en route.

1159
01:16:11,203 --> 01:16:14,354
Good. Okay, gentlemen,
the limo is on its way.

1160
01:16:14,563 --> 01:16:18,556
These are the squibs. Two controllers,
one in each pocket.

1161
01:16:18,763 --> 01:16:23,518
Now, a squeeze or a sharp tap
sets them off. Do you understand?

1162
01:16:24,443 --> 01:16:27,196
How do you do? I'm the best man.

1163
01:16:27,403 --> 01:16:30,395
Hello. My name's Peter. I'm the best man.

1164
01:16:30,563 --> 01:16:33,760
I work at Mark and Spencer's.
I love chocolate biscuits.

1165
01:16:33,923 --> 01:16:36,357
Oh, Mumsy, I want some ginger beer!

1166
01:16:41,603 --> 01:16:43,195
Here she is!

1167
01:16:43,883 --> 01:16:46,443
Here's the bride! Hi, pretty!

1168
01:16:46,683 --> 01:16:48,162
Oh, my God!

1169
01:16:52,763 --> 01:16:55,152
Not much of a job though, is it, Vinnie?

1170
01:17:03,483 --> 01:17:05,075
Thank you so much.

1171
01:17:09,083 --> 01:17:10,402
My leg!

1172
01:17:15,523 --> 01:17:18,356
Testing, one, two, three. Do you read?

1173
01:17:18,603 --> 01:17:22,232
Testing, one, two, three.
Do you read? Do you read?

1174
01:17:22,443 --> 01:17:24,957
Remember, we'll need Graziosi
loud and clear.

1175
01:17:25,123 --> 01:17:27,398
-You got lots of time.
-Only until the speeches.

1176
01:17:27,483 --> 01:17:29,201
Right. After the dancing and dessert.

1177
01:17:29,283 --> 01:17:32,958
This is an ltalian wedding.
The speeches are before the dinner.

1178
01:17:33,203 --> 01:17:34,682
You knew that, right?

1179
01:17:36,323 --> 01:17:37,802
You still got plenty of time.

1180
01:17:37,883 --> 01:17:41,319
Plenty of time?
You have 10 minutes if you're lucky!

1181
01:17:42,243 --> 01:17:45,155
This is not a problem. Gonna be okay.

1182
01:17:46,403 --> 01:17:47,802
We have a problem.

1183
01:17:51,003 --> 01:17:53,153
"And Michael Andrew Felgate...

1184
01:17:53,403 --> 01:17:57,442
"...do you take Gina Maria Vitale
for your lawful wife...

1185
01:17:57,723 --> 01:17:59,395
"...to have and to hold...

1186
01:17:59,683 --> 01:18:02,834
"...from this day forward,
for better, for worse...

1187
01:18:03,043 --> 01:18:04,920
"...for richer, for poorer...

1188
01:18:05,123 --> 01:18:08,752
"...in sickness and in health,
until death do you part?"

1189
01:18:09,003 --> 01:18:10,072
I do.

1190
01:18:10,523 --> 01:18:13,242
"You have declared your consent
before the Church.

1191
01:18:13,443 --> 01:18:15,399
"May the Lord in His goodness...

1192
01:18:15,483 --> 01:18:19,192
"...strengthen your consent
and fill you both with His blessings.

1193
01:18:19,443 --> 01:18:20,319
"Amen.

1194
01:18:20,443 --> 01:18:24,834
"ln the name of the Father
and the Son and the Holy Spirit...

1195
01:18:25,083 --> 01:18:27,802
"...l pronounce you husband and wife."

1196
01:18:29,563 --> 01:18:31,201
You may kiss the bride.

1197
01:18:47,163 --> 01:18:49,233
Hey! Wedding! Smile!

1198
01:18:50,403 --> 01:18:51,836
Wedding!

1199
01:18:53,443 --> 01:18:55,593
Kitchen team, we've got one shot at this.

1200
01:18:55,683 --> 01:18:58,117
And less than five minutes
before the speeches.

1201
01:18:58,203 --> 01:18:59,397
We got it.

1202
01:19:00,163 --> 01:19:01,312
About the other day--

1203
01:19:01,403 --> 01:19:04,236
I don't want to hear.
I'm sure you had your reasons.

1204
01:19:04,323 --> 01:19:07,076
No names, no pack drill. That's my motto.

1205
01:19:07,323 --> 01:19:09,154
That's incredibly nice of you.

1206
01:19:09,243 --> 01:19:11,199
Goodness, are you drinking?

1207
01:19:11,843 --> 01:19:13,834
-Come on, darling.
-I've only had one glass.

1208
01:19:13,923 --> 01:19:15,754
-Let me take that.
-She thinks I'm drunk!

1209
01:19:15,843 --> 01:19:17,959
You're very embarrassing
when you're drunk.

1210
01:19:23,403 --> 01:19:24,961
I think you're on now.

1211
01:19:32,043 --> 01:19:33,442
In position.

1212
01:19:34,243 --> 01:19:38,395
I just wanted to say how sorry I am
about your son.

1213
01:19:39,323 --> 01:19:40,551
Thank you.

1214
01:19:42,523 --> 01:19:44,161
This is a happy day.

1215
01:19:44,483 --> 01:19:46,041
I wish you much joy.

1216
01:19:46,883 --> 01:19:49,602
I especially look forward to the speeches.

1217
01:19:53,603 --> 01:19:56,481
You're very kind,
and I appreciate the way you've...

1218
01:19:57,403 --> 01:19:59,598
...opened my eyes to new possibilities.

1219
01:19:59,683 --> 01:20:01,275
As a matter of fact...

1220
01:20:01,563 --> 01:20:04,396
...l recently thought of a new idea
that I think...

1221
01:20:04,803 --> 01:20:06,873
...could be profitable to us both.

1222
01:20:08,923 --> 01:20:10,754
Absurdly profitable, really.

1223
01:20:11,203 --> 01:20:13,114
I mean, we're talking millions.

1224
01:20:15,483 --> 01:20:18,361
But this isn't the occasion
to be talking business.

1225
01:20:18,523 --> 01:20:19,956
Another time perhaps.

1226
01:20:20,043 --> 01:20:22,113
Thank you so much for being here.

1227
01:20:23,163 --> 01:20:24,357
He's lost his mind.

1228
01:20:24,443 --> 01:20:27,003
And speeches in 04:05.

1229
01:20:28,683 --> 01:20:30,162
Are you out of your mind?

1230
01:20:30,243 --> 01:20:32,074
-He wasn't ready. Relax.
-Relax?

1231
01:20:32,163 --> 01:20:33,596
Congratulations!

1232
01:20:35,323 --> 01:20:37,917
In five minutes, we're dead.
You, me and Gina.

1233
01:20:38,203 --> 01:20:39,682
Never chase the bid.

1234
01:20:39,803 --> 01:20:40,713
What?

1235
01:20:40,923 --> 01:20:43,118
Let the bid come to you.
It's rule number one.

1236
01:20:43,203 --> 01:20:45,353
What the hell are you talking about?

1237
01:20:45,603 --> 01:20:48,037
Mr. Graziosi wants to see you over there.

1238
01:20:48,323 --> 01:20:50,075
Of course. A pleasure.

1239
01:20:53,243 --> 01:20:55,598
I think we're in business.

1240
01:20:55,803 --> 01:20:56,918
Speeches in three.

1241
01:20:59,683 --> 01:21:02,072
We have to go say hi to Maria.

1242
01:21:05,723 --> 01:21:10,080
So basically you continue to sell
and buy interesting work through us...

1243
01:21:11,003 --> 01:21:14,040
...and I do the insurance valuation
on the collection.

1244
01:21:14,443 --> 01:21:17,799
Like insurance against a fire, for example.

1245
01:21:18,563 --> 01:21:20,235
Fires can happen.

1246
01:21:20,443 --> 01:21:21,876
Look at Sotheby's.

1247
01:21:24,163 --> 01:21:27,951
But fortunately, of course,
you would be handsomely covered.

1248
01:21:29,283 --> 01:21:30,682
What do you think?

1249
01:21:35,043 --> 01:21:36,601
Are we in business?

1250
01:21:38,923 --> 01:21:40,356
-Say it!
-In two.

1251
01:21:42,283 --> 01:21:43,875
Michael! There you are!

1252
01:21:45,283 --> 01:21:46,636
You look serious.

1253
01:21:47,003 --> 01:21:48,038
Cheer up!

1254
01:21:48,163 --> 01:21:50,472
Those are quite something. Mind if l--

1255
01:21:50,603 --> 01:21:52,753
-Take it easy.
-It's quite all right.

1256
01:21:55,363 --> 01:21:56,762
What do you think?

1257
01:21:56,843 --> 01:21:59,516
Philip, this is Uncle Vito.

1258
01:21:59,723 --> 01:22:00,792
Delighted to meet you.

1259
01:22:00,883 --> 01:22:02,521
You from the old country?

1260
01:22:04,963 --> 01:22:06,601
My family's from Sicily.

1261
01:22:08,803 --> 01:22:10,156
Land of the goat.

1262
01:22:10,243 --> 01:22:12,711
My wife and I spent
a wonderful week there.

1263
01:22:12,803 --> 01:22:16,000
Charming little pensione
with a priceless little owner...

1264
01:22:16,163 --> 01:22:17,801
...who looked just like a Mafiosi.

1265
01:22:17,883 --> 01:22:20,317
We called him AI Capone.
Remember, darling?

1266
01:22:22,043 --> 01:22:24,159
These things are making me squiffy!

1267
01:22:25,643 --> 01:22:27,838
Thank you. Excuse me.

1268
01:22:29,723 --> 01:22:31,281
I'm sorry, Philip. Uncle Vito!

1269
01:22:31,363 --> 01:22:34,480
I am a ninny!
I forgot to tell you the good news.

1270
01:22:34,683 --> 01:22:38,676
Mr. Morganson here has decided
Cromwell's are the team for him.

1271
01:22:41,763 --> 01:22:43,082
That's marvelous news.

1272
01:22:43,163 --> 01:22:45,074
We must meet and discuss the details.

1273
01:22:45,163 --> 01:22:47,518
Let me just find my--

1274
01:22:54,403 --> 01:22:57,713
I'll have Helen leave a message on Monday.
Excuse me.

1275
01:22:58,843 --> 01:23:02,802
What a horrible thing to happen.
I'm sure he meant it as a joke.

1276
01:23:03,003 --> 01:23:05,437
Could I borrow him for a second? Thanks.

1277
01:23:07,363 --> 01:23:10,400
That was quite something.
I love party tricks.

1278
01:23:11,963 --> 01:23:15,638
Pray gather round
from the farthest reaches!

1279
01:23:16,323 --> 01:23:17,881
And take your seats...

1280
01:23:18,443 --> 01:23:20,877
...to hear the speeches!

1281
01:23:20,963 --> 01:23:22,874
And the speeches are early.

1282
01:23:28,283 --> 01:23:30,353
Listen, I swear to God I'll do it.

1283
01:23:30,963 --> 01:23:35,002
I'm begging you, for Gina's sake,
let me wait till the party's over.

1284
01:23:35,283 --> 01:23:38,241
During the speeches. For Gina's sake.

1285
01:23:44,043 --> 01:23:45,362
Please, we have to hurry.

1286
01:23:45,443 --> 01:23:48,799
I'm going as fast as I can,
but it's rather a mess.

1287
01:23:49,083 --> 01:23:51,597
Turn around. I need to tuck it in properly.

1288
01:23:54,083 --> 01:23:56,392
English. Figured as much.

1289
01:23:56,883 --> 01:24:00,762
Just shove it in there. Shove it in there!
God! No, stuff it in!

1290
01:24:02,523 --> 01:24:03,956
Give me your gun.

1291
01:24:05,723 --> 01:24:07,634
Give me your gun, Frank.

1292
01:24:14,683 --> 01:24:15,877
Johnny's.

1293
01:24:16,283 --> 01:24:20,162
His first. I want you to use this one.

1294
01:24:23,203 --> 01:24:24,875
I think he gave Frank a live gun.

1295
01:24:24,963 --> 01:24:27,079
-I suggest abort. I repeat, abort!
-No!

1296
01:24:27,683 --> 01:24:30,117
We can still get this. Get a mike in there.

1297
01:24:30,203 --> 01:24:33,718
Kitchen team, get into position,
but nobody goes in until I say so.

1298
01:24:33,803 --> 01:24:34,952
-Sir.
-Shut up!

1299
01:24:35,043 --> 01:24:36,317
Copy that.

1300
01:24:40,763 --> 01:24:43,038
Best man. How do you do?

1301
01:24:43,363 --> 01:24:46,912
Excuse me, but I rather think
you're wilting there, old boy.

1302
01:24:47,163 --> 01:24:48,516
There we are.

1303
01:24:48,603 --> 01:24:50,275
There we are.

1304
01:24:51,483 --> 01:24:52,677
Welcome back.

1305
01:24:54,843 --> 01:24:55,912
See you later, then.

1306
01:24:56,003 --> 01:24:57,914
Ladies and gentlemen...

1307
01:24:58,003 --> 01:25:01,313
...perhaps you'd like to give a big hand...

1308
01:25:01,603 --> 01:25:04,037
...to Gina and Mike!

1309
01:25:12,963 --> 01:25:15,636
You gotta get in here. It's too late.
He's gonna die.

1310
01:25:16,163 --> 01:25:18,631
No. This has been nine years.
Kitchen team.

1311
01:25:18,843 --> 01:25:19,992
Standing by.

1312
01:25:20,123 --> 01:25:21,442
Wait for my word.

1313
01:25:33,163 --> 01:25:36,041
We still got a chance. Frank's got a mike.

1314
01:25:36,283 --> 01:25:37,272
But....

1315
01:25:38,003 --> 01:25:38,958
What?

1316
01:25:39,963 --> 01:25:41,760
Vito gave him a live gun.

1317
01:25:46,403 --> 01:25:47,916
All right. All right.

1318
01:25:48,123 --> 01:25:51,479
Now, can your clapping,
'cause here's you know whom:

1319
01:25:51,603 --> 01:25:54,322
My new brother and our bridegroom.

1320
01:25:54,523 --> 01:25:56,275
All right. Come on.

1321
01:25:56,363 --> 01:25:58,513
Mikey, we're waiting!

1322
01:25:59,323 --> 01:26:00,881
We're waiting, Mikey!

1323
01:26:01,083 --> 01:26:04,280
You're getting married. Thattaboy!

1324
01:26:16,723 --> 01:26:17,758
Speak up!

1325
01:26:19,123 --> 01:26:20,397
Sorry.

1326
01:26:22,443 --> 01:26:24,001
This is making me nervous.

1327
01:26:24,083 --> 01:26:26,153
The last time I spoke at a wedding...

1328
01:26:26,243 --> 01:26:29,315
...l was supposed to propose a toast
to the bridesmaids.

1329
01:26:29,443 --> 01:26:31,593
I ended up proposing an opening bid.

1330
01:26:31,683 --> 01:26:33,639
What's worse is they both sold.

1331
01:26:34,563 --> 01:26:36,235
Want it in the head or the chest?

1332
01:26:36,323 --> 01:26:38,553
Come on. Come on!

1333
01:26:41,283 --> 01:26:43,353
-So I'll keep it simple.
-Good idea!

1334
01:26:43,443 --> 01:26:47,197
Andjust tell you why I think today,
for once...

1335
01:26:47,603 --> 01:26:50,037
...l'm the one acquiring the masterpiece.

1336
01:26:52,323 --> 01:26:55,679
Firstly, I've always been a huge fan
of the ltalian school.

1337
01:26:58,963 --> 01:27:00,476
Come on, speak to me.

1338
01:27:01,843 --> 01:27:03,196
It's not working.

1339
01:27:04,243 --> 01:27:08,600
They say that the real test
of a masterpiece...

1340
01:27:08,923 --> 01:27:11,756
...is whether you instinctively know
it's something...

1341
01:27:12,163 --> 01:27:13,835
...you'll keep forever...

1342
01:27:14,283 --> 01:27:15,716
...love forever.

1343
01:27:19,203 --> 01:27:21,592
Don't think of it as gaining a son.

1344
01:27:21,763 --> 01:27:23,242
Ifyou don't do it...

1345
01:27:23,323 --> 01:27:24,676
...you're losing a daughter.

1346
01:27:24,763 --> 01:27:26,719
-Sir?
-No good.

1347
01:27:28,643 --> 01:27:30,235
In some cases....

1348
01:27:31,083 --> 01:27:32,755
In some cases...

1349
01:27:32,963 --> 01:27:36,797
...it's even something you'd be prepared
to die to protect.

1350
01:27:38,603 --> 01:27:40,434
That's certainly the case here.

1351
01:27:40,643 --> 01:27:43,203
I'd rather die than see any harm
come to Gina.

1352
01:27:44,123 --> 01:27:46,512
I love her more than my own life.

1353
01:27:48,323 --> 01:27:52,316
And I hope I'm making myself crystal clear
on that point.

1354
01:27:54,123 --> 01:27:55,351
Death...

1355
01:27:55,643 --> 01:27:57,440
...is okay by me.

1356
01:28:01,443 --> 01:28:04,480
And now, ladies and gentlemen,
the fa ther of the bride.

1357
01:28:11,003 --> 01:28:13,119
For chrissakes, Bob, this is it.

1358
01:28:13,283 --> 01:28:15,239
Damn it! Kitchen team, go!

1359
01:28:27,203 --> 01:28:29,717
Excuse me! FBl!

1360
01:28:50,443 --> 01:28:52,001
It's bullshit!

1361
01:28:52,483 --> 01:28:53,438
Do it!

1362
01:28:53,843 --> 01:28:54,719
-Do it!
-No!

1363
01:28:55,883 --> 01:28:57,475
-Vinnie, do it!
-Vinnie, no!

1364
01:28:58,363 --> 01:28:59,955
Do it! Do it!

1365
01:29:00,043 --> 01:29:00,919
No.

1366
01:29:01,123 --> 01:29:02,397
Vinnie, do it!

1367
01:29:02,923 --> 01:29:04,436
I'm ordering you! Kill her!

1368
01:29:04,523 --> 01:29:06,036
Yes! Got him!

1369
01:29:07,043 --> 01:29:09,238
FBl! Freeze!

1370
01:29:11,083 --> 01:29:11,913
No!

1371
01:29:22,763 --> 01:29:24,435
Ambulance, now!

1372
01:29:24,643 --> 01:29:25,837
It's too late!

1373
01:29:54,723 --> 01:29:56,520
Let's go! The party's over!

1374
01:30:03,843 --> 01:30:05,401
-On three.
-I'm ready!

1375
01:30:26,243 --> 01:30:27,801
I'm sorry.

1376
01:30:28,123 --> 01:30:30,000
-I'm so sorry.
-No, I'm sorry.

1377
01:30:31,643 --> 01:30:33,918
You should both be sorry.

1378
01:30:37,083 --> 01:30:39,358
These things are surprisingly painful.

1379
01:30:39,843 --> 01:30:40,673
My God!

1380
01:30:40,803 --> 01:30:42,714
It's a new rule of mine:

1381
01:30:42,883 --> 01:30:45,477
Always assume you guys
are hiding something.

1382
01:30:46,963 --> 01:30:47,759
Why--

1383
01:30:47,883 --> 01:30:51,842
When I thought of you with a gun,
Michael, suddenly I wanted a backup.

1384
01:30:52,043 --> 01:30:53,396
You did good.

1385
01:30:57,283 --> 01:30:58,352
Oh, my God!

1386
01:30:58,723 --> 01:30:59,917
I'll tell you, Frank...

1387
01:31:00,003 --> 01:31:02,801
...her father might act
like a moron sometimes....

1388
01:31:04,803 --> 01:31:05,952
So I retired.

1389
01:31:06,363 --> 01:31:07,591
I'm telling you, Frankie...

1390
01:31:07,683 --> 01:31:09,082
...the kid's a genius.

1391
01:31:09,163 --> 01:31:10,596
I mean, think about it.

1392
01:31:10,683 --> 01:31:13,436
You got Vito.
Vito thinks he got his revenge.

1393
01:31:13,803 --> 01:31:16,795
And that's it. Badda-bing. You're even.

1394
01:31:17,083 --> 01:31:19,358
You're in the clear. All of you.

1395
01:31:19,523 --> 01:31:22,754
-How the hell could you do this to me?
-You were gonna do it to me.

1396
01:31:22,843 --> 01:31:25,198
-We did it because we love you.
-Same here.

1397
01:31:25,403 --> 01:31:26,392
What?

1398
01:31:26,603 --> 01:31:28,798
You love both of us?

1399
01:31:32,923 --> 01:31:34,641
I don't think so, Michael.

1400
01:31:37,883 --> 01:31:38,793
Oh, my God.

1401
01:31:38,883 --> 01:31:40,953
-Wasn't that the--
-Oh, my God!

1402
01:31:42,403 --> 01:31:44,234
Welcome to the halfway point...

1403
01:31:44,323 --> 01:31:48,032
...in the annual Central Park
Senior Marathon.

1404
01:31:51,683 --> 01:31:54,277
-Leave me alone!
-Wait! Listen. Listen!

1405
01:31:54,523 --> 01:31:56,479
This picture, it isn't me.

1406
01:31:56,683 --> 01:31:59,322
It's Kansas City Little
Big Mickey Blue Eyes!

1407
01:31:59,523 --> 01:32:02,321
I was pretending to be a mobster,
and couldn't say my R's...

1408
01:32:02,403 --> 01:32:05,281
...and I had to kiss the waitress
or they would've killed us!

1409
01:32:05,363 --> 01:32:07,035
Look who's sitting next to me.

1410
01:32:08,363 --> 01:32:09,921
Recognize that suit?

1411
01:32:10,523 --> 01:32:11,717
Is that Dad?

1412
01:32:11,963 --> 01:32:14,079
This photo means nothing.

1413
01:32:16,643 --> 01:32:18,713
-So who's Mickey Blue Eyes?
-I am.

1414
01:32:19,243 --> 01:32:21,996
I mean, I was. We just made him up.

1415
01:32:22,203 --> 01:32:24,114
Come back and I'll explain everything.

1416
01:32:24,203 --> 01:32:27,878
So when you said you were
with my dad that day, you were--

1417
01:32:28,123 --> 01:32:30,193
I was telling the truth.

1418
01:32:32,123 --> 01:32:35,081
-You told me a lot of other lies.
-I know.

1419
01:32:35,323 --> 01:32:39,236
I know. I thought it was the only way
to keep you.

1420
01:32:39,723 --> 01:32:41,156
But you were right.

1421
01:32:41,443 --> 01:32:43,638
It was the only sure way to lose you.

1422
01:32:49,643 --> 01:32:51,679
-I was right.
-You were.

1423
01:32:51,843 --> 01:32:54,403
-And smarter than you all along.
-Yes.

1424
01:32:54,923 --> 01:32:56,993
-And braver.
-Much.

1425
01:32:57,723 --> 01:32:59,475
And more convincing at being shot.

1426
01:32:59,683 --> 01:33:00,911
Infinitely.

1427
01:33:03,083 --> 01:33:04,516
Marry me, Gina.

1428
01:33:07,043 --> 01:33:09,273
Would I have to be Mrs. Blue Eyes?

1429
01:33:11,243 --> 01:33:12,392
Come here....

1430
01:33:13,163 --> 01:33:14,118
What?

1431
01:33:14,563 --> 01:33:15,712
Come here.

1432
01:33:17,123 --> 01:33:18,556
-What?
-It's me.

1433
01:33:18,643 --> 01:33:20,474
Mickey Blue.

1434
01:33:21,643 --> 01:33:22,792
Oh, please!

1435
01:37:51,083 --> 01:37:54,075
Subtitles: Boomerang

